<TITLE> Nasir steers Under-19s home </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Dec 15 (bdnews24.com)  An all-round performance from Nasir Hossain powered the Bangladesh Under-19 team to a convincing 44-run win over the Sri Lankan counterparts in the third one-dayer at Shaheed Chandhu Stadium Saturday. The home side now enjoy a 2-1 lead in the five-match series. The Sri Lanka Under-19 team were wrapped up for 159 in 45.3 overs as pacer Dollar Mahmud (3/24), Nasir Hossain (2/9) and SM Shakil (2/38) wrecked the opponents' innings. Zenith top-scored with 47, followed by Priris on 29 and Pathirana on 28. Earlier, Bangladesh posted a modest total of 203 all out in 49.3 overs after choosing to bat first. Nadimuddin Mintu struck a superb 66 runs while Nasir and Ashraful Aziz chipped in with 41 and 26 to help the home side go beyond the 200-mark. The fourth and fifth matches are billed for Monday and Tuesday respectively. 
